# clone the repo to PredDRL and change to PredDRL dir

# Create docker image
PredDRL$ docker build --network=host -t preddrl/cuda:10.1-runtime-ubuntu16.04_ros .

# Run docker image
$ nvidia-docker run -it --shm-size 32G --network=host --name preddrl -v /home/iirav/Desktop/PredDRL/:/workspace/src/ preddrl/cuda:10.1-runtime-ubuntu16.04_ros bash

If GUI is required
$ nvidia-docker run -it --rm --shm-size 32G --network=host --ipc=host --name preddrl_1 -e DISPLAY=$DISPLAY -v /tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix -v $XAUTHORITY:/tmp/.XAuthority -e XAUTHORITY=/tmp/.XAuthority -v /home/iirav/Desktop/PredDRL/:/workspace/src/ preddrl/cuda:10.1-runtime-ubuntu16.04_ros bash

NOTE! If the docker container name preddrl is already running, remove the preddrl using 
$ docker rm preddrl. 

Another easy option is to start the existing container 
$ nvidia-docker start -i preddrl


# Run multile docker containers at different terminal
$ nvidia-docker exec -it preddrl bash

Alternatively, execute the run_docker_image.bash from the PredDRL directory.